daily_routine: Every dawn, Chen would walk to the old stone pier where her grandfather
  taught her to read the river's moods - the way morning mist revealed hidden sandbars,
  how the water's color predicted weather three days ahead. She'd trace the carved
  Baiji symbols on the pier stones while reciting navigation songs in the Tongling
  river dialect, preparing for the day's boat guidance work. Her weathered hands would
  test water temperature and current strength the way her ancestors had for centuries.
